Commentary.Commentary: We are back for the final session of Day 2. The Bangladesh players are out in the middle. Kraigg Brathwaite and John Campbell will open the innings for West Indies. Mustafizur Rahman will start the proceedings for Bangladesh.
... Day 2, Session 3 ...

Right then! Bangladesh are right on top. In the final session of Day 2, they will hope that they can take a few wickets and put the visitors on the back foot. West Indies, on the other hand, need to bat and bat long if they want to get close to this total. It won't be easy on a spinning wicket. Let's see what happens. Join us in a while to find out.

West Indies, on the other hand, did not have a good outing. At the end of Day 1, they might have felt that the match was nicely poised but on Day 2 so far, they have faltered. They were just unable to pick up the wickets and suffered. Jomel Warrican was the pick of the bowlers for them while he was well supported by Roach and Cornwall. Gabriel had a disappointing outing. Overall, it was a poor peformance and they would need to bat really well.

Bangladesh would be very happy with the performance. They started well but then some quick wickets towards the end of Day 1 meant that they shared the honours on Day 1. Shadman Islam scored a fine fifty while many batsmen got starts. Shakib Al Hasan threw his wicket away after reaching 50 but it was Mehidy Hasan who carried on and on, reaching his maiden century in the process and taking Bangladesh to 430. A brilliant performance from the hosts.

A superb batting performance from Mehidy Hasan has taken Bangladesh to 430! It is a very good score on a tough wicket to bat on. Bangladesh will be a very happy side at the moment and they will feel that they are on top at the moment. West Indies would need to bat really well to get close to the score. TEA HAS BEEN TAKEN AS WELL.

We are set to begin the second session of Day 2. The West Indies players are out in the middle. Taijul Islam and Mehidy Hasan will resume their innings for Bangladesh. Jomel Warrican will start the proceedings for this session.
... Day 2, Session 2 ...

Bangladesh will be a happy side at the moment. This pitch is not an easy one to bat on and they have scored past 300 and will be looking to score as many more as they can. Shakib Al Hasan played well before he threw away his wicket before Lunch. Mehidy Hasan has played really well and is on the verge of a fifty. He is joined by Taijul Islam and would look to add more runs post Lunch. They are in a very strong position and would want to continue the advantage. An exciting session 2 awaits us. Join us at 1210 local (0610 GMT) for the second session.

West Indies started the day really well as they sent back Liton Das very early on but since then they were not able to take many wickets. They tried hard and bowled tightly but were not rewarded. They did take the wicket of Shakib towards the end but it was too late. They should have had the wicket of Mehidy Hasan as well if they had not dropped him when he was on 24. Post the Lunch break, the visitors would hope to prize out the remaining wickets as quickly as possible.

An interesting session comes to an end! Bangladesh would be the happier side at the break but they will be slightly disappointed that they lost Shakib Al Hasan towards the end of the session. West Indies bowled well but they could have had more wickets if Shayne Moseley had not dropped a catch of Mehidy Hasan. Overall, a very engrossing session of play.

With the ball, West Indies would be pleased with the way they bowled. Roach, Gabriel and Mayers all bowled good line and lengths, whereas Cornwall and Warrican kept it simple to sustain the pressure. However, only Roach and Warrican managed to get into the wickets. The former getting a wicket and the latter getting three.

Opting to bat after winning the toss, Bangladesh started on a positive note before they lost Tamim Iqbal. Then Shadman Islam and Najmul Hossain Shanto stitched a 43-run stand before Shanto was run out in a poor fashion. But Shadman continued to play his game as he stitched a 53-run stand with Mominul Haque. Just when it seemed like these two will continue to bat on and on, both got dismissed in quick succession. But if West Indies felt they were getting on top, Mushfiqur and Shakib thwarted them off. Rahim fell but Liton Das then joined Shakib and they ensured to end the day on a high. Bangladesh also managed to score over 100 runs in the final session.

What a day of Test match cricket we have had. There was even contest between bat and ball and both the batsmen as well as the bowlers enjoyed the conditions. Overall, Bangladesh take the honours on Day 1.

... DAY 1, SESSION 2...

Right then! The post-Lunch session would be an interesting one to see with regards to how the game goes on. Will West Indies go onto get further inroads? Or will Bangladesh continue to build on from here? Join us for the post-Lunch session in about 40 minutes.

West Indies started with Roach and Gabriel as they tried to take the early advantage from the surface. Roach though was good with his lines and lengths but Gabriel was a bit wayward at the start as he sprayed a lot down leg. For his consistency Roach got the wicket for Tamim Iqbal as Rakheem Cornwall bowled superbly getting some turn and bounce from the wicket. Kyle Mayers was good in his first outing in a Test as he too bowled tight lines and lengths. Roach not only bowled right lines and lengths but was sharp in the field too as he effected a run of Najmul Hossain Shanto. Overall a good session for the visitors with the ball.

After electing to bat first, Bangladesh started on the right note as Islam hit the first ball of the match for a boundary. Both the openers saw off the initial 4 overs but Tamim was unlucky to not continue as he dragged one onto the wickets. Then Shadman Islam and Najmul Hossain Shanto were involved in a 43-run stand before a mixup ended Hossain Shanto's stay at the crease, a few minutes before session close.

We are all set to begin as the West Indies players make their way out to the middle. The two Bangladesh openers, Tamim Iqbal and Shadman Islam are out in the middle. For the West Indies, Kemar Roach will start with the ball. Here we go...

Bangladesh skipper, Mominul Haque says that they will  bat first because the wicket looks good and they can put up some runs. Further says that it is very important to be in a good stead before the Test match. Further mentions that they are going with just one pacer and three spinners.

After thumping the West Indies in the limited-overs format the tour moves ahead to the red-ball format as Bangladesh take on the Men in Maroon in the Test series involving two matches. Welcome to the first day of the first Test. Bangladesh though start as favourites as they are fielding a strong unit against a depleted West Indies side which misses a few names including their regular skipper, Jason Holder. Can West Indies cater the spin challenge of Bangladesh and put up a fight? They though would be happy with how their batsmen fared in the tour game and would want them to perform in the first Test and the series as well. Who will take the opening day honours? Stay tuned to find out who won the toss and what are the team compositions of the two sides in a short while.

Right then! West Indies are 5 down and still trail by 241 runs. Will they be able to bat out another session? How much can they reduce the lead? We will find out in the post lunch session which will begin at 1210 local (0610 GMT).

For Bangladesh, Taijul Islam, Nayeem Hasan and Mehidy Hasan were the wicket takers as they bowled relentlessly at the West Indies batsmen and frustrated them with tight lines and lengths. They got assisted from the surface too  as it started playing its tricks offering vicious turn and bounce. Bangladesh would be encouraged to continue with it's spin triplets for another session and gets the remaining wickets quickly.

Resuming on the overnight score of 75/2 West Indies lost Nkrumah Bonner on the very first ball when he edged one to the slips. Since then skipper, Kraigg Brathwaite and Kyle Mayers managed to get the Windies innings on track with a 55-run stand as Braithwaite got to his 20th Test fifty too in the process. Just when these two looked to settle out well in the middle. A horrible error of judgement from Brathwaite saw him lose his off pole. Soon Mayers too followed his skipper back to the hut. Since then, Blackwood and Da Silva managed to survive a few nervy moments as they survived the passage to the lunch.

An intriguing session comes to an end. 33 overs were bowled as West Indies managed to score 114 runs but also lost three wickets including that of Bonner who was dismissed on the first ball of the day. All in all Bangladesh would be the happier of the two.

After Bangladesh managed to post a score above 400 in the first innings, West Indies were in a lot of pressure as they lost a couple of wickets during the fag end of Day 2. The good thing for them is their skipper, Kraigg Brathwaite is still out there and he is going strong. Still trailing by 355 runs with 8 wickets in hand. It will take a herculean effort for the West Indies batsmen to scale this score and then take the lead. Hello and welcome to the Day 3 of this Test match. Also known as the moving day which potentially decides in which direction the game is heading. Though the ball is still in Bangladesh's court and they would look to skittle out West Indies by spinning a web with their spinners. While the West Indies' would look to bat out the day and take session by session to decide how to go about their business. To know how the day pans out stay tuned as the action begins shortly.

Right then! That's the end of Day 2! Bangladesh are on top and they would want to continue the momentum. West Indies, on the other hand, would want to bat and bat long on Day 3. Join us at 0930 local (0330 GMT) for the start of Day 3. Till then, cheers and take care.

Bangladesh's bowling was superb as Mustafizur starred with the ball with two wickets. The spinners had their say as they troubled Brathwaite and Bonner throughout but they were not rewwarded. They would want to take early wickets on Day 3. They are well ahead in the game and would not want to give the visitors a chance.

With the bat, West Indies started poorly as they lost 2 wickets in quick succession but Kraigg Brathwaite and Nkrumah Bonner stuck in and they faced the Bangla bowlers well and these two are looking very solid in the middle. They need to continue though and build a strong partnership on Day 3.

West Indies did not bowl all that well. They started well picking up the wicket of Liton Das but then they faltered and they gave away too many runs for their liking. The Bangladesh batsmen milked them for runs for fun and they were given a severe punishment.

He fell but Mehidy Hasan scored a magnificent century to take Bangladesh to 430. He was well supported by the lower order and they ended up with a huge total.

An excellent day comes to an end for Bangladesh! They will be a very happy side and they are well on top in this game! Brathwaite and Bonner did well to survive the final few overs before Stumps but they would know that they are well behind the game and they need to put up a strong show on Day 3.

Hello and a warm welcome to the 4th day's play between Bangladesh and West Indies. Just two days left but this game has moved at a fast pace with Bangladesh moving ahead in the game. They are leading by 218 runs and are holding all the cards at the moment. The question on everyone's mind is what target will the hosts set West Indies. So, Day 3 ends with the game moving steadily. Still, a lot of time left in the game as we don't know who has the upper hand in the game. How will Day 4 unfold? What target will Bangladesh be hoping to set for the West Indies to chase? All answers will unfold on Day 4 when the game begins at  0930 local (0330 GMT). Till then cheers and take care.

For Bangladesh with the ball, it was  Mehidy Hasan who bagged 4 wickets as Nayeem Hasan, Taijul Islam and Mustafizur Rahman bagged a couple each. They were just relentless in the field. Bowling tight lines and lengths and asking a question to the batsmen on every ball.  Though they would be disappointed to have dropped a few chances and some of the chances flew past their fielders. But overall it was the effort of their spinners that handed them the advantage in the game.

Earlier after coming out to bat at 75/2 West Indies began shockingly as they lost Nkrumah Bonner on the first ball of the day. Since that wicket, Kraigg Brathwaite and Kyle Mayers put up a 55-run stand as Brathwaite went past his 20th Test fifty but could not convert it into a ton as he departed owing to an error in judgement. Mayers too followed soon after. Putting Jermaine Blackwood and Joshua Da Silva in a precarious situation. The duo first saw a few overs before Lunch and when they came back after Lunch they started to score freely. As Blackwood went past his fifty and both the batsmen were involved in a 99-run stand. Just at the stroke of Tea, West Indies lost both of them and after Tea when the play resumed they just collapsed. Folding for 259 runs and handing a huge lead of 171 runs to Bangladesh.

West Indies would be happy with the ball as they managed to get 3 quick wickets to keep them in the hunt after a shoddy batting from their lower order handed the advantage back to the hosts. Cornwall's double strike in his first over did not allow Bangladesh to implode and the wicket of Shadman Islam forced the hosts to adopt the defensive way.

Bangladesh would be disappointed with their batting in the second innings as they lost 3 wickets to get themselves under pressure. Though they would also be happy that the lead is well over 200 and when they come out to bat of Day 4 they would look to add some quick runs and look for a target close to 350 for the West Indies to chase.

What an engrossing day of Test match we have had today. The bowlers dominating, then the batsmen fighting it out and amidst all this runs were scored. Bangladesh might be marginally ahead but West Indies are still in the game and they would look to get the pendulum swing in their favour when they come out on Day 4.

That is it from this game! West Indies take a 1-0 lead in this two-match Test series. The second Test between West Indies and Bangladesh will be held in Dhaka on 11th February, 2021. Do join us for that at 0930 local (0330 GMT). Till then, take care and cheers!

Kraigg Brathwaite, West Indies skipper, says they believed in themselves to chase this down. Adds that they believed in their plans and it paid off. Credits Mayers for his solid display of batting in the fourth innings. Further says that he himself should have batted well and given them a start to chase this total. Brathwaite says that they had the belief in themselves to chase this total down.

Kyle Mayers is named the Man of the Match. He says that he is a positive person. Adds that he is happy with his knock. Mentions it gives him pride for playing with West Indies. Further says that this knock will motivate the youngsters.

Mominul Haque, Bangladesh skipper, says that he is disappointed with the team's performance. Credits Mayers for his excellent knock. Further says that the spinners normally gets help on Day 5 but they could not stop the Windies batters from scoring. Mentions Mehidy Hasan batted well and bowled well in the first innings. Ends by saying they will look to make a comeback in the next Test.

When West Indies started the chase, they did not get off to a great start as they lost their openers when the score was under 50. Moseley also did not survive for long. Then came the big partnership between Bonner and Mayers. They stitched a solid 216-run stand to bring West Indies some hope in this chase. Bonners departed for 86 but Mayers kept on piling the runs and wanted to stay till the end. He did it and in the process scored an unbeaten 210 to help West Indies register their highest fourth innings run-chase in Asia. Stay tuned for the presentation...

Bangladesh got a lead of 170 runs after bowling out West Indies for 259 in their first innings. Mominul Haque scored a hundred and his partnership with Liton Das was crucial for them in giving West Indies a target of 395. Cornwall and Jomel Warrican were the pick of the bowlers for West Indies as they took 6 wickets between them in that innings.

Coming to West Indies, Brathwatie was the highest scorer for them in their first innings where he made 76. Blackwood scored 68 but did not last longer. Mehidy Hasan was the pick of the bowlers for the hosts as he took 4 wickets. Taijul Islam supported him and took 2 wickets.

Earlier, Bangladesh had scored 430 runs in the first innings where Mehidy Hasan was the top-scorer for them in that innings. Shakib Al Hasan and Shadman Islam scored fifties but could not convert that into a ton. Jomel Warrican was the pick of the bowlers for the West Indies as he picked 4 wickets. Cornwall did not look that threatening as he took 2 wickets.

Kyle Mayers showed excellent grit and determination for West Indies to win this match for them. His shots were superb and his timing was excellent. He never got bogged down when wickets were falling in the final session today. He kept one end intact and kept on scoring the runs.

For Bangladesh, their bowlers toiled hard but could not get the crucial wickets. They could not dismiss Mayers who was looking solid out there. Nayeem Hasan and Mehidy Hasan tried their best. They broke the 216-run stand between Mayers and Bonner but after that they could not get wickets at regular intervals.

What a victory this has been for West Indies. Take a bow, Kyle Mayers! It was a fantastic innings from him on his debut Test. His partnership with Nkrumah Bonner set up the chase for them. Then when Bonner departed, Blackwood started well but perished early after playing a poor shot. Da Silva gave good support and almost sealed the chase for West Indies.

Hello and welcome to Day 5 of the first Test between Bangladesh and West Indies in Chattogram. The hosts are 7 wickets away from a victory and would look to wrap up things as soon as possible. Mehidy Hasan has been the pick of the bowlers as he took 3 wickets. On the other hand, West Indies need 285 runs more to win the match. Kyle Mayers and Nkrumah Bonner are looking good. The visitors would want this partnership to continue. Stay tuned for a while.
... Day 5, Session 1 ...

Right then! West Indies need 285 more runs to win and it will be interesting to see what will be their approach on Day 5! Will they go for the win or will they go for a draw? Bangladesh, on the other hand, need just 7 wickets and they would hope that they can get the remaining wckets as quickly as possible. The fifth day's play will begin on 7th February 2021 at 9.30 am local (0330 GMT). The build-up will begin much before that. Till then, cheers and take care.

Russell Domingo, the Bangladesh coach, is there for a chat. He says that Mominul Haque and Liton Das batted well and they are sure that they will achieve the victory on Day 5. Goes onto say that Mehidy Hasan has carried his form from the ODI series. Tells that he works really hard and is pleased with his performance. Goes onto say that they still have work to do and not bowl bad balls on Day 5. Tells that they cannot be too unhappy with the way things have gone so far. States that they have very good facilities and they want to make sure that the young players get the best opportunity to perform. Informs that their performance away from home has not been good and they need to improve that. Tells that Shakib has a bit of a niggle and they want to give him the best opportunity to recover before the next Test match. Mentions that Mominul is still learning the trade and he knows that he has got some work to do and he is leading through his performances at the moment.

Earlier in the day, Mominul Haque's century and his partnership with Liton Das helped Bangladesh get a lead of 394. Mominul was brilliant while Liton Das was positive. They lost some wickets in a heap and then declared with a massive lead. West Indies' bowling was not upto the mark and they were punished by the batters. Rahkeem Cornwall was the pick of the bowlers. Overall, it was a good day for Bangladesh!

Bangladesh, on the other hand, had a good time with the ball. They started poorly but once they introduced Mehidy Hasan into the attack, things started to happen. Mehidy Hasan picked up all the three wickets to fall and has been superb. Taijul Islam and Nayeem Hasan bowled threatening lines and lengths but they have not been rewarded yet. They need 7 wickets to win and have one full day in hand to get there. That's a lot of time and with the pitch playing some tricks, Bangladesh would hope that they can take a 1-0 lead in the 2-match Test series.

Post-Tea, West Indies needed a good start but they did not get that as they first lost John Campbell to Mehidy Hasan. Kraigg Brathwaite followed him soon after giving a catch to short leg and West Indies were in compete tatters at that moment. The agony was yet to come as they lost Shayne Moseley for a cheap score but since then, Kyle Mayers and Nkrumah Bonner have played superbly and took West Indies to Stumps without any further loss of wickets. They are 285 runs behind and a tough day awaits them on Day 5.

Excellent day for Bangladesh but one might feel that West Indies have made a slight comeback with the current partnership between Kyle Mayers and Nkrumah Bonner! They still have a long way to go but they will be pleased that at least they are showing a fight. Bangladesh, on the other hand, are still ahead and they would not be too disappointed with the work done.

After declaring with a lead of 394, Bangladesh would have wanted to pick up a few wickets before Tea but that did not happen as the West Indian openers played them really well. Mustafizur Rahman has bowled good lines and lengths while Taijul Islam has been on the shorter side a touch. They are way ahead in the game and they still have a lot of time to go to bowl the visitors out. They will aim to prize out a few wickets before the end of the day. Join us at around 2.30 pm local (0830 GMT) for the final session.

A session which has belonged to Bangladesh but West Indies will be happy that they managed to survive the few overs before the break without losing a wicket. Kraigg Brathwaite and John Campbell came out and have looked very solid so far and have not played any rash shots. They still have a long way to go and they need to start all over again after Tea. They have a tough job in their hands and they would hope that they can bat for long periods.
